  "prompt": "How many lokas (like heaven, hell, earth etc.) are there according to Hindu mythology?",
  "response": "According to Hindu mythology, there are traditionally 14 lokas or planes of existence:\n\nHigher Lokas (Upper Planes):\n1. Satya Loka (Brahma Loka) - Realm of ultimate truth\n2. Tapa Loka - Realm of spiritual energies\n3. Jana Loka - Realm of enlightened beings\n4. Mahar Loka - Realm of great sages\n5. Svarga Loka - Heavenly realm\n6. Bhuvar Loka - Atmospheric/intermediate realm\n\nLower Lokas (Lower Planes):\n7. Bhur Loka - Physical/earthly plane\n8-14. Seven Patala Lokas (Netherworlds):\n- Atala\n- Vitala\n- Sutala\n- Talatala\n- Mahatala\n- Rasatala\n- Patala (lowest realm)\n\nThese lokas are believed to represent different levels of consciousness, spiritual evolution, and existential planes. The concept suggests that beings can be reborn or exist in different realms based on their karma and spiritual development.\n\nThe most commonly known lokas are Svarga (heaven), Bhur Loka (earth), and the Patala Lokas (underworlds).",
